I"…<p>The <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/finite-state-dynamical-systems-are-diverse">Markov</a> property describes a <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/dynamical-systems-have-a-certain-anatomy">system</a> in which the current <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/body-states-modulate-feelings">state</a> is completely determined by the previous one. It argues that all information necessary to describe a new state is contained in the previous one, meaning that the <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/dynamical-systems-have-memory">entire memory of dynamical systems is contained in the current state</a>.</p>
